<p>Yesterday, I went to see <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Muppets_Take_Manhattan">The Muppets Take Manhattan</a> at the Museum of the Moving Image. The Muppets are ageless and always relatable, as were the people who came to the viewing - all ages, colors, and sizes - just like the muppets themsleves.</p>
<p>As Pete said, &ldquo;We&rsquo;re all just people.&rdquo;</p>
